It’s really unclear what the left means when they claim to be all in it for “marginalized communities,” but it’s likely safe to assume they mean a group of people they’ve decided deserve special treatment. Nonetheless, it feels a bit insulting to honor these communities with what many consider “really ugly” art, which is why JD Vance said what everyone is thinking.

It is weird to me that these people don't see the irony of honoring "marginalized communities" by making a beautiful historical building really ugly.
title: JD Vance Blasts Church of England For “Really Ugly” Display Honoring “Marginalized Communities”
